summary: When I saw a guest writer would be on Web, I got worried. Guests haven’t... had the best history with Spider-Man. I mean, they...
body:
When I saw a guest writer would be on Web, I got worried. Guests haven’t… had the best history with Spider-Man. I mean, they weren’t bad at what they did, but Jack Kirby (back when artists had weight on the stories) basically wrote a Fantastic Four story with Spidey as a guest in his own mag, adhering to the tradition of making “guests” assholes, and Tony Isabela wrote a Peter Parker who would mock a teenage girl about her eating disorder, so, yeah, not the best characterization around. Not to mention the horror of how Erik Larsen handled him in Marvel Comics Presents.

However, I actually liked how Kurt Busiek handled him. I mean, yeah, he played it safe, with one-shots emotionally led by original characters and minimal interventions by Peter Parker rather than Spider-Man, but all in all, it was good. I wish he’d stayed a bit longer. Kinda curious about what he would have done if he had to commit to the character.
